review_blob:
On tap at the Side Street Cafe in Bar Harbor.
Aroma-nice balance of grain and spicy hops.
Appearance-thin white head, pale yellow, very clear.
Flavor-some biscuity malt backed by a firm hop bitterness. Clean
Mouthfeel-fairly thin, decent carbonation, crisp on the palate
Overall-decent session beer. thirst quenching brew, great for a hot summer day

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
Pours black with a small tight head. Sour cherry nose, very tart. Flavor is sour stone fruits, vanilla and oak. Lingers on the palate for a very pleasing finish.
beer_name: Captain Lawrence Barrel Select Mother Barrel

review_blob:
Opaque. Not much of a head. Nose has sweet chocolate and dark fruits. Roast coffee and chocolate dominate the flavor profile. Silky smooth on the tongue. You'd never guess this is 11%+ abv. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Nice amber color with a thick white head. Aroma is a good balance of citrus hops and malt. Flavor is also well balanced with a good grainy malt base supporting the hops. A nice session ale that doesn't overwhelm your palate

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Clean roast aroma. Silky, malty flavor with chocolate finish. Above average brown ale

Aroma-Hop forward nose with predominantly citrus notes
Appearance-nice red color, clear with a frothy head
Taste-nicely balanced, bold hop character with a clean finish
Palate-medium body.
Overall-flavorful brew, very drinkable

Aroma-some spicy and pine notes well balanced with bready malt background
Appearance-deep amber with a good healthy head
Taste-strong English malt backbone is very pleasant. light sweetness, medium bitterness
Palate-medium body, average carbonation, finishes cleanly
Overall-very drinkable brew.
